Not every person with grey hair at the Coast is a sorcerer. Youths in some areas should stop targeting innocent elderly persons purporting them to be witches and wizards. The elderly have to constantly look over their shoulder in their own city for fear of being lynched by rowdy youths alleging the old practice black magic. The local administration should make arrests to put an end to the deadly mindset. The youths should not take the law into their hands. The trend is becoming prevalent and authorities must stop the criminal activities.  Mombasa